<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">reset:&nbsp; ; Reset vector points here<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; standard NES init<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ...<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; Determine whether system is NTSC or PAL<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  lda $2002&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; clear VBL flag<br />wvbl:Â  Â lda $2002<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  bpl wvbl<br /><br />Â  Â  Â  Â  ldx #52Â  Â  Â  Â  Â ; 29799 delay<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  ldy #24<br />dly:Â  Â  dex<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  bne dly<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  dey<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  bne dly<br />Â  Â  Â  Â <br />Â  Â  Â  Â  lda $2002&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; high bit set if NTSC, clear if PAL<br />Â  Â  Â  Â  sta ntsc_if_neg<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ...<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; Later, where you need to do different things for NTSC and PAL:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bit ntsc_if_neg<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; bmi ntsc<br />pal:&nbsp; &nbsp; ...<br /><br />ntsc:&nbsp; &nbsp;...</div>
